<title>
EVAP Canister Purge Valve Inspection
</title>
<attention1>
<ptxt>
Do not use your mouth to apply vacuum to EVAP canister purge valve. Fuel vapor is harmful.
</ptxt>
</attention1>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Do not apply vacuum more than –66 kPa (–0.67 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, –9.57 psi, –0.66 bar); otherwise EVAP canister purge valve could be damaged.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<s1>
<ptxt>
With ignition “OFF”, disconnect connector and hoses from EVAP canister purge valve (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove purge valve from air cleaner assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check resistance between two terminals of purge valve.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace EVAP canister purge valve.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
EVAP canister purge valve resistance
</title>
<ptxt>
30 to 34 Ω at 20 &#176;C (68 &#176;F)
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8T401122005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "41.573mm" ver = "01" gw = "139" gh = "101"/>
</figure>
</spec>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check EVAP canister purge valve operation as follows.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
If faulty condition is found, replace EVAP canister purge valve.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Install special tool and vacuum hose (2) to purge valve (1).
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L1B003">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09917-47011">
09917–47011
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
With 12 V battery connected to purge valve terminals, check that vacuum (–60 kPa, –0.6 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, –8.7 psi, –0.6 bar) cannot be applied to purge valve.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
With no 12 V battery connected to purge valve terminals, check that vacuum (–60 kPa, –0.6 kgf/cm<sup>2</sup>, –8.7 psi, –0.6 bar) can be applied to purge valve.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A121006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "94.326mm" ver = "01" gw = "162" gh = "251"/>
